  Month 10 opens Quarter IV — The Second Conjunction. The Sulphur work here is
  the most sophisticated practical work of Year Two and directly anticipates Year
  Three's mineral Sulphur work. Ensure students understand the distinction between
  plain distillation (separation) and rectification (purification by repeated
  distillation) — many confuse the two. The border cohobation with vegetable
  Sulphur over mineral salt should be treated as an experimental preparation, not
  a consumable product. Document everything; judge nothing prematurely.
]

